<TITLE> Mother dies, 3 infants missing after Buriganga collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 6 (bdnews24.com)A mother drowned in the Buriganga River on Sunday, while her nine-year-old son and two other infants remain missing, after an overloaded passenger boat capsized in the crowded waterway after colliding with a sand laden trawler. "The boat was travelling to Sadarghat from Pagla Ghat in Narayanganj with 60 to 70 passengers," Abul Kalam, sub-inspector of South Keraniganj Police Station, told bdnews24.com. The body of a 29-year-old woman identified as Rahima was recovered from the river in the evening, while her 9-year-old son Arif and two other infants, 9-year-old Nazma and 4-year-old Yamin are still missing, said Kalam. He said all other passengers on the boat survived the incident. bdnews2
